docs.abstract: The administration isn’t letting the tech giants write the rules of global trade. Good.
docs.snippet: The administration isn’t letting the tech giants write the rules of global trade. Good.
docs.lead_paragraph: One reason that the idea of free trade has fallen out of fashion in recent years is the perception that trade agreements reflect the wishes of big American corporations, at everybody else’s expense.

headline.main: How the Biden Administration Took the Pen Away From Meta, Google and Amazon
headline.print_headline: A New Policy at Last Favors People Over Big Tech

docs.abstract: A board member who was part of Sam Altman’s ouster as chief executive joined a majority of the company’s staff in calling for the decision’s reversal.
docs.snippet: A board member who was part of Sam Altman’s ouster as chief executive joined a majority of the company’s staff in calling for the decision’s reversal.
docs.lead_paragraph: The future of OpenAI is in jeopardy after more than 700 of its 770 employees signed a letter on Monday saying they may leave the company for Microsoft if the ousted chief executive, Sam Altman, is not reinstalled at the high-profile artificial intelligence start-up.

headline.main: OpenAI Staff Threatens Exodus, Jeopardizing Company’s Future
headline.print_headline: OpenAI Future Unclear At Threat of Walkouts

docs.abstract: Science fiction writers and A.I. researchers have long feared the machine you can’t turn off.
docs.snippet: Science fiction writers and A.I. researchers have long feared the machine you can’t turn off.
docs.lead_paragraph: Science fiction writers and artificial intelligence researchers have long feared the machine you can’t turn off. The story goes something like this: A powerful A.I. is developed. Its designers are thrilled, then unsettled, then terrified. They go to pull the plug, only to learn the A.I. has copied its code elsewhere, perhaps everywhere.

headline.main: The Unsettling Lesson of the OpenAI Mess
headline.print_headline: The Lesson of the OpenAI Mess

docs.abstract: Sam Altman, the most prominent promoter of artificial intelligence, learned that it’s hard to be a visionary founder like the Apple legend.
docs.snippet: Sam Altman, the most prominent promoter of artificial intelligence, learned that it’s hard to be a visionary founder like the Apple legend.
docs.lead_paragraph: Steve Jobs, driven by his genius and his gut, invented the iPhone and built Apple into the world’s most valuable company. He was uncompromising, larger than life and irreplaceable. His life was creating the future, which would be filled with devices controlled by their users.

headline.main: The Long Shadow of Steve Jobs Looms Over the Turmoil at OpenAI
headline.print_headline: OpenAI Strife Recalls Story Of Steve Jobs

docs.abstract: In a blog post, Mr. Altman said he would focus on improving products and building a new board, which added Microsoft as a nonvoting member.
docs.snippet: In a blog post, Mr. Altman said he would focus on improving products and building a new board, which added Microsoft as a nonvoting member.
docs.lead_paragraph: OpenAI said on Wednesday that it had completed the first phase of a new governance structure that added Microsoft as a nonvoting board member, as it works to end the divisions that fueled the ouster of Sam Altman as chief executive and sets itself up for a future as a bigger company.

headline.main: Back at OpenAI, Sam Altman Outlines the Company’s Priorities
headline.print_headline: Back at OpenAI Helm, Altman Outlines Company’s Priorities

docs.abstract: The OpenAI drama is an extreme case of an old concern in business.
docs.snippet: The OpenAI drama is an extreme case of an old concern in business.
docs.lead_paragraph: People are going to be talking about the blowup at OpenAI for years. ChatGPT itself — a product of OpenAI — could not have concocted a tale as wild as the one that unfolded over the weekend.

headline.main: What Happens When a Founder Leaves?

docs.abstract: Mira Murati, who previously served as chief technology officer, has been named interim chief executive.
docs.snippet: Mira Murati, who previously served as chief technology officer, has been named interim chief executive.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sam Altman, the high-profile chief executive of OpenAI, who became the face of the tech industry’s artificial intelligence boom, was pushed out of the company by its board of directors, OpenAI said in a blog post on Friday afternoon.

headline.main: OpenAI’s Board Pushes Out Sam Altman, Its High-Profile C.E.O.

docs.abstract: A poll generated by artificial intelligence, embedded next to a Guardian article on Microsoft’s news aggregator platform, asked readers to speculate on the cause of a woman’s death.
docs.snippet: A poll generated by artificial intelligence, embedded next to a Guardian article on Microsoft’s news aggregator platform, asked readers to speculate on the cause of a woman’s death.
docs.lead_paragraph: An auto-generated poll that Microsoft embedded on its news aggregating platform alongside a Guardian article was “crass” and caused significant damage to The Guardian’s reputation, the newspaper said on Thursday.

headline.main: Microsoft Criticized for Embedding ‘Crass’ A.I. Poll Beside News Article
headline.print_headline: Microsoft Blasted for A.I. Poll Placed Near Guardian Article

docs.abstract: Sam Altman confronted a member over a research paper that discussed the company, while directors disagreed for months about who should fill board vacancies.
docs.snippet: Sam Altman confronted a member over a research paper that discussed the company, while directors disagreed for months about who should fill board vacancies.
docs.lead_paragraph: Before Sam Altman was ousted from OpenAI last week, he and the company’s board of directors had been bickering for more than a year. The tension got worse as OpenAI became a mainstream name thanks to its popular ChatGPT chatbot.

headline.main: Before Altman’s Ouster, OpenAI’s Board Was Divided and Feuding
headline.print_headline: OpenAI Faced Bitter Divide Before Firing
